title.narrative: By 2021, National Partners have strengthened technical and management capacity to sustain high-impact maternal, neonatal and child health interventions, focusing on the most vulnerable communities.

description.narrative: UNICEF's support to the Ministry of Health resulted in: 146,377 children being immunized against measles and rubella through routine immunization; 37,385 pregnant women receiving at least four antenatal care contacts and 58,222 deliveries attended by a health worker; 217,909 children treated for acute respiratory infection and screened for tuberculosis, 81,640 treated for diarrhoea and 11,351 for malaria. Outreach services to hard-to-reach communities were enhanced through logistical support (including three new mobile clinic vehicles procured by UNICEF) and over 90 ‘barefoot doctors' revitalized by the Government to provide health care in remote communities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
